From fb53f4e0b37ecdbc82ad659d4b1d235f78fbb789 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aneesh Pradhan <apradhan5@horizon.csueastbay.edu>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 23:08:13 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] perry: ship msm8937 camera platform stack from montana

hw_get_module failed with ENOENT because camera.msm8937.so (and the
mm-qcamera/MCT/ISP libs) were never packaged. BoardConfig pulled empty
montana BoardConfigVendor.mk but device.mk never inherited montana's
blob makefile.

Pull the shared SoC camera stack via camera-vendor.mk. Sensor/chromatix
libs remain a separate XT1765 stock extract (imx219/s5k4h8/ov5695).
---
 camera-vendor.mk      | 108 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 device.mk             |   4 ++
 proprietary-files.txt |   5 ++
 3 files changed, 117 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 camera-vendor.mk

diff --git a/camera-vendor.mk b/camera-vendor.mk
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..f433a2e
--- /dev/null
+++ b/camera-vendor.mk
@@ -0,0 +1,108 @@
